  "text": "November 2012 and only involving gamblers and their families and/or friends. This excluded accesses by other users, for example, members of the professional community. Online counselling is conducted using an interview based on the diagnostic protocol of Ladouceur and colleagues [CITATION_1] . It is a semistructured clinical interview based on DSM-IV criteria and composed of 26 questions on pathological gambling. In addition to the diagnostic criteria described in the DSM-IV, the interview investigates other aspects such as the reasons for the consultation, the events that have led to the decision, information on how you obtained your gambling habits, details of the gambling problem, and the presence of other addictions.",
